---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceDetail from '../../../components/ServiceDetail.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Salesforce Experience Cloud: portals, communities and self-service"
  description="Resolve IT builds Salesforce Experience Cloud portals: customer portals, partner portals and self-service environments that relieve your team and empower your clients."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', item: '/en' }, { name: 'Services', item: '/en/diensten' }, { name: 'Experience Cloud', item: '/en/diensten/experience-cloud' }]}
>
  <ServiceDetail
    lang="en"
    eyebrow="Service · Experience Cloud"
    title="Give customers and partners their own space, in your brand"
    intro="Salesforce Experience Cloud lets you build branded portals for customers, partners and employees. From self-service knowledge bases to dealer or customer portals that let you serve hundreds of relationships at scale, without burdening your support team."
    heroStats={[{ num: 'Branded', label: 'portals' }, { num: 'Self-', label: 'service at scale' }, { num: '300+', label: 'projects' }]}
    image="/images/diensten/experience-cloud.jpg"
    whatTitle="Less support load, higher customer satisfaction"
    whatText={[
      'Every support ticket a customer can resolve themselves via a portal is one less for your team. Experience Cloud provides the building blocks for a portal that looks professional, integrates seamlessly with your Salesforce data and genuinely helps customers move forward.',
      'We build portals for a range of use cases: customers viewing their own cases, contracts and invoices; partners registering deals and receiving leads; employees handling HR processes through self-service.',
    ]}
    whatList={[
      'Customer portals with case and contract visibility',
      'Partner portals for deal registration and lead distribution',
      'Knowledge bases and self-service FAQs that reduce support load',
      'Fully in your brand identity, on your domain',
    ]}
    deliverablesTitle="What you get"
    deliverables={[
      { icon: '🏗️', title: 'Custom portal', text: 'An Experience Cloud environment configured for your specific audience and use case, in your brand identity.' },
      { icon: '🔐', title: 'Authentication & access control', text: 'Secure login for customers or partners, with granular permissions at object level.' },
      { icon: '📚', title: 'Knowledge base & self-service', text: 'Knowledge articles, FAQs and flows that let customers act independently without burdening your team.' },
      { icon: '📊', title: 'Portal analytics', text: 'Insight into which pages are visited, what questions arise and where customers get stuck.' },
    ]}
    steps={[
      { title: 'Use-case definition', text: 'We determine which portal type delivers most value and which audience it is primarily intended for.' },
      { title: 'Architecture & permissions', text: 'Setup of portal structure, user profiles, object and field permissions, and login flow.' },
      { title: 'Build & styling', text: 'We build the pages in Experience Builder, apply your brand identity and build the required components.' },
      { title: 'Testing & go-live', text: 'UAT with end users, performance checks and go-live with support.' },
    ]}
    why={[
      { icon: '🎨', title: 'Your brand, your portal', text: 'We build portals that look professional and fit seamlessly with the rest of your digital environment, with no generic Salesforce look.' },
      { icon: '⚡', title: 'Built on your data', text: 'The portal shows real-time data from your Salesforce environment. No synchronisation hassle, no outdated information.' },
      { icon: '📉', title: 'Lower support load', text: 'A well-built portal structurally reduces incoming tickets. We measure the baseline and demonstrate the impact.' },
    ]}
    faqs={[
      { q: 'What is the difference between Experience Cloud and a regular website?', a: 'An Experience Cloud portal is connected to your Salesforce data. Customers see their own cases, contracts or invoices in real time: something a regular website cannot offer. For <a href="/en/cases/staff-capital">Staff Capital</a> we built a portal where clients see in real time what is happening with their own workforce.' },
      { q: 'Can customers create cases through the portal?', a: 'Yes. Case management is one of the most-used Experience Cloud features. Customers create a case, track the status and communicate with your team, all in the same portal.' },
      { q: 'Is Experience Cloud suitable for a partner network?', a: 'Absolutely. Partner Community is one of three standard Experience Cloud templates and offers deal registration, lead distribution and MDF management out of the box.' },
      { q: 'How long does it take to build a portal?', a: 'A simple customer portal is live within 6–8 weeks. More complex portals with custom components and integrations take 3–5 months. <a href="/en/contact#afspraak">Schedule a call</a> for an estimate. For <a href="/en/cases/multa-casting">MULTA Casting</a>, for example, we built two fully pixel-perfect communities, one for candidates and one for clients.' },
    ]}
  />
</Layout>
